{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778984045192,"sessionID":"ses_1cc49cb2affepFEBRfr82gW1Mc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_92tFSIGY9pT1lb8H6zEnVjM9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"```\\nergothioneine biosynthetic process (GO:0052699) [2 direct EXP]\\n|__ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via gamma-glutamyl-hercynylcysteine sulfoxide (GO:0052704) [4 EXP] [only in bacteria]\\n|__ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via hercynylcysteine sulfoxide synthase (GO:0140479) [0 EXP][only in Fungi]\\n```\\n\\nid: GO:0052699\\nname: ergothioneine biosynthetic process\\ndef: \\\"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ergothioneine, a naturally occurring metabolite of histidine with antioxidant properties.\\\" [Wikipedia:Ergothioneine]\\nintersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:134344 ! ergothioneine(1+)\\n\\nid: GO:0052704\\nname: ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via gamma-glutamyl-hercynylcysteine sulfoxide\\ndef: \\\"The pathway resulting in the formation of ergothioneine from histidine via a set of steps in which gamma-glutamyl-hercynylcysteine sulfoxide is formed as an intermediate.\\\" [PMID:4276459, PMID:5484456]\\nis_a: GO:0052699 ! ergothioneine biosynthetic process\\n\\nid: GO:0140479\\nname: ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via hercynylcysteine sulfoxide synthase\\ndef: \\\"A biosynthetic process that results in the formation of ergothioneine from histidine via a set of steps including the hercynylcysteine sulfoxide synthase reaction, which converts N-alpha,N-alpha,N-alpha-trimethyl-L-histidine directly to hercynylcysteine sulfoxide.\\\" [PMID:22209968, PMID:24828577]\\nis_a: GO:0052699 ! ergothioneine biosynthetic process\\n\\n\\nThe child terms map to these two MetaCyc variant pathways:\\nergothioneine biosynthesis I (bacteria) (PWY-7255) = GO:0052704\\nergothioneine biosynthesis II (fungi) () (PWY-7550) = GO:0140479\\n\\nSo, these could be added as exactMatch xrefs to the two child terms.\\n\\nHowever, these specific variant pathways are really beyond scope of GO (they can be represented as GO-CAMs if necessary) so it would be better to obsolete the two child ter... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [],\n4:   \"title\": \"Obsoletion request: ergothioneine biosynthetic process terms\",\n5:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/32018\"\n6: }\n\n(End of file - total 6 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"```\\nergothioneine biosynthetic process (GO:0052699) [2 direct EXP]\\n|__ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via gamma-glutamyl-hercynylcysteine sulfoxide (GO:0052704) [4 EXP] [only in bacteria]\\n|__ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via hercynylcysteine sulfoxide synthase (GO:0140479) [0 EXP][only in Fungi]\\n```\\n\\nid: GO:0052699\\nname: ergothioneine biosynthetic process\\ndef: \\\"The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ergothioneine, a naturally occurring metabolite of histidine with antioxidant properties.\\\" [Wikipedia:Ergothioneine]\\nintersection_of: GO:0009058 ! biosynthetic process\\nintersection_of: has_primary_output CHEBI:134344 ! ergothioneine(1+)\\n\\nid: GO:0052704\\nname: ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via gamma-glutamyl-hercynylcysteine sulfoxide\\ndef: \\\"The pathway resulting in the formation of ergothioneine from histidine via a set of steps in which gamma-glutamyl-hercynylcysteine sulfoxide is formed as an intermediate.\\\" [PMID:4276459, PMID:5484456]\\nis_a: GO:0052699 ! ergothioneine biosynthetic process\\n\\nid: GO:0140479\\nname: ergothioneine biosynthesis from histidine via hercynylcysteine sulfoxide synthase\